# LOG ANALYZER

This test project is a tool for analyzing logs in JSON format using modern Python tools. The script reads the log file(s), processes the data and generates reports in a convenient tabular form.

## Installation

### [`Install uv!`](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/getting-started/installation/)

###### Or you can use requirements.txt if you like

### Clone repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/VEGAMETA/LOG_ANALYZER.git
cd LOG_ANALYZER
```

## Run example

```bash
uv run main.py -f ./logs/example1.log ./logs/example2.log -r average
```

## Need some help?!

```bash
uv run main.py -h
```

### Base syntax

```bash
uv run main.py --file <file1> [<file2> ...] --report <report_type> [--date <date>]
```

### Prompt parameters

| Param        | Description                                |
| ------------ | ------------------------------------------ |
| -f, --file   | Path to your report file(s)                |
| -r, --report | Report types (see below)                   |
| -d, --date   | [Optional] Date filter, format: YYYY-DD-MM |

Report types:

- average - avg. response time for endpoints
- user-agent(TODO) - user-agent (TBD)

### Test

This project is using `pytest`

```bash
uv run pytest
```
